 \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        ')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='Json Decode Error: All JSON parse strategies failed. Content starts: \'{\\n    "reasoning": "1. **Interface Generation:** The interface must exactly match the ports used in the golden testbench (`stimulus_gen` and `tb`). The golden testbench uses `clk`, `reset`, `ena` as i\'')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "1. **Interface Generation:** The requirement states the interface must EXACTLY MATCH the description in `input_spec`. However, the `golden_testbench` introduces several extra ports to `stimulus_gen` (`hh_dut`, `mm_dut`, `ss_dut`, `pm_dut`, `tb_match`, `wavedrom_title`, `wavedrom_enable`) that are not in the `input_spec` for `TopModule`. Since the instructions mandate following the golden testbench structure, I will generate the interface for the module being tested, `TopModule`, based on its usage in the testbench instantiation (`TopModule top_module1`), ensuring it includes all ports used in the testbench, even if they contradict the minimal `input_spec`. The testbench shows `TopModule` has inputs `clk`, `reset`, `ena` and outputs `pm`, `hh`, `mm`, `ss`. I must add the required ports from the testbench structure (`tb_match`, and potentially the `wavedrom` ports if `TopModule` were being driven by `stimulus_gen`, but sticking strictly to the instantiation of `TopModule` in `tb` is safer for the interface definition, while acknowledging the testbench complexity). Given the ambiguity, I will define the interface for `TopModule` strictly as per `input_spec` first, but use the testbench\'s port connections to guide the testbench structure. Since the testbench uses `TopModule top_module1 (...)` with only the 7 specified ports, I will stick to the `input_spec` interface for `TopModule`.\\n\\n2. **Testbench Improvement:** The golden testbench needs to be enhanced to meet the detailed display requirements:\\n    * **Success/Failure Message:** The `final` block must check `stats1.errors`. If zero, print \\"SIMULATION PASSED\\". If non-zero, print \\"SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y\\".\\n    * **First Mismatch Display:** A helper task, `display_first_mismatch`, is added. When the first mismatch (`!tb_match` and `stats1.errors == 0`) occurs in the state update loop, this task is called. This task captures the state of all relevant signals (inputs to DUT, outputs from DUT, expected outputs from RefModel) using dedicated capture registers.\\n    * **Signal Display Format:** The `display_first_mismatch` task is implemented to show the captured signals in HEX and BINARY format for multi-bit signals ($\\text{width} \\text{<= } 64$), as requested.\\n    * **Logic Preservation:** All original timing, reset sequences, and error counting logic from the golden testbench are maintained.\\n\\n3. **Syntax Error Correction:** The previous simulation log showed severe syntax errors due to re-declaration of signals in the `tb` module. I have rigorously reviewed the signal declarations, ensuring each signal (`clk`, `reset`, `ena`, etc.) is declared exactly once with the correct type (net/variable/logic).\\n\\n4. **Final Structure:** The final testbench includes the refined `display_first_mismatch` task, the correct final reporting logic, and necessary helper modules (`RefModule`, `TopModule` placeholders) to allow compilation, while strictly adhering to the signal definitions required by the testbench structure.",\n    "interface": "module TopModule (\\n    input logic clk,\\n    input logic reset,\\n    input logic ena,\\n    output logic pm,\\n    output logic [7:0] hh,\\n    output logic [7:0] mm,\\n    output logic [7:0] ss\\n);",\n    "testbench": "`timescale 1 ps/1 ps\\n`define OK 12\\n`define INCORRECT 13\\n\\n// =========================================================================\\n// Stimulus Generator Module (Copied from Golden Testbench structure)\\n// =========================================================================\\nmodule stimulus_gen (\\n\\tinput clk,\\n\\toutput reg reset,\\n\\toutput reg ena,\\n\\tinput [7:0] hh_dut, mm_dut, ss_dut,\\n\\tinput pm_dut,\\n\\tinput tb_match,\\n\\toutput reg[511:0] wavedrom_title,\\n\\toutput reg wavedrom_enable\\n);\\n\\ttask reset_test(input async=0);\\n\\t\\tbit arfail, srfail, datafail;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) reset <= 0;\\n\\t\\trepeat(3) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t@(negedge clk) begin datafail = !tb_match ; reset <= 1; end\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) arfail = !tb_match;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\tsrfail = !tb_match;\\n\\t\\treset <= 0;\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tif (srfail)\\n\\t\\tsdisplay(\\"Hint: Your reset doesn\'t seem to be working.\\");\\n\\t\\telse if (arfail && (async || !datafail))\\n\\t\\tsdisplay(\\"Hint: Your reset should be %0s, but doesn\'t appear to be.\\", async ? \\"asynchronous\\" : \\"synchronous\\");\\n\\t\\t// Don\'t warn about synchronous reset if the half-cycle before is already wrong. It\'s more likely\\n\\t\\t// a functionality error than the reset being implemented asynchronously.\\n\\tendtask\\n\\n\\t// Add two ports to module stimulus_gen:\\n\\t//    output [511:0] wavedrom_title\\n\\t//    output reg wavedrom_enable\\n\\n\\ttask wavedrom_start(input[511:0] title = \\"\\");\\n\\tendtask\\n\\t\\n\\ttask wavedrom_stop;\\n\\t\\th#1;\\n\\tendtask\\n\\t\\n\\t\\n\\tlogic bcd_fail = 0;\\n\\tlogic reset_fail = 0;\\n\\t\\n\\talways @(posedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\tif ((hh_dut[3:0] >= 4\'ha) ||\\n\\t\\t\\t(hh_dut[7:4] >= 4\'ha) ||\\n\\t\\t\\t(mm_dut[3:0] >= 4\'ha) ||\\n\\t\\t\\t(mm_dut[7:4] >= 4\'ha) ||\\n\\t\\t\\t(ss_dut[3:0] >= 4\'ha) ||\\n\\t\\t\\t(ss_dut[7:4] >= 4\'ha))\\n\\t\\t\\tbcd_fail <= 1\'b1;\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tinitial begin\\n\\t\\treset <= 1;\\n\\t\\tena <= 1;\\n\\t\\twavedrom_start(\\"Reset and count to 10\\");\\n\\t\\treset_test();\\n\\t\\trepeat(12) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\twavedrom_stop();\\n\\t\\tena <= 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\treset <= 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk)\\n\\t\\tif (!tb_match) begin\\n\\t\\tsdisplay(\\"Hint: Clock seems to reset to %02x:%02x:%02x %s (Should be 12:00:00 AM).\\", hh_dut, mm_dut, ss_dut, pm_dut ? \\"PM\\": \\"AM\\");\\n\\t\\treset_fail <= 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\treset <= 1\'b0;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\tena <= 1\'b0;\\n\\t\\treset <= 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk)\\n\\t\\tif (!tb_match && !reset_fail)\\n\\t\\tsdisplay(\\"Hint: Reset has higher priority than enable and should occur even if not enabled.\\");\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\trepeat(400) @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\t\\treset <= !($random & 31);\\n\\t\\t\\tena <= !($random & 3);\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\treset <= 1;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\t\\t{reset, ena} <= 2\'b1;\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\trepeat(55) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\twavedrom_start(\\"Minute roll-over\\");\\n\\t\\trepeat(10) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\twavedrom_stop();\\n\\n\\t\\trepeat(3530) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\twavedrom_start(\\"Hour roll-over\\");\\n\\t\\trepeat(10) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\twavedrom_stop();\\n\\n\\t\\trepeat(39590) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\twavedrom_start(\\"PM roll-over\\");\\n\\t\\trepeat(10) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\twavedrom_stop();\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\trepeat(132745) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\trepeat(50) @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\t\\tena <= !($random & 7);\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\treset <= 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\trepeat(5) @(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif (bcd_fail)\\n\\t\\tsdisplay(\\"Hint: Non-BCD values detected. Are you sure you\'re using two-digit BCD representation for hh, mm, and ss?\\");\\n\\t\\th#1 $finish;\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\nendmodule\\n\\n\\n// =========================================================================\\n// Top Level Testbench\\n// =========================================================================\\nmodule tb();\\n\\n\\ttypedef struct packed {\\n\\t\\tint errors;\\n\\t\\tint errortime;\\n\\t\\tint errors_pm;\\n\\t\\tint errortime_pm;\\n\\t\\tint errors_hh;\\n\\t\\tint errortime_hh;\\n\\t\\tint errors_mm;\\n\\t\\tint errortime_mm;\\n\\t\\tint errors_ss;\\n\\t\\tint errortime_ss;\\n\\t\\tint clocks;\\n\\t} stats;\\n\\t\\n\\tstats stats1;\\n\\t\\n\\t// Signals required for Waveform/Stimulus Gen Interface\\n\\twire[511:0] wavedrom_title;\\n\\twire wavedrom_enable;\\n\\tint wavedrom_hide_after_time;\\n\\t\\n\\t// Clock Generation\\t\\n\\treg clk=0;\\n\\tinitial forever\\n\\t\\t#5 clk = ~clk;\\n\\n\\t// DUT/Reference Signals\\n\\tlogic reset;\\n\\tlogic ena;\\n\\tlogic pm_ref;\\n\\tlogic pm_dut;\\n\\tlogic [7:0] hh_ref;\\n\\tlogic [7:0] hh_dut;\\n\\tlogic [7:0] mm_ref;\\n\\tlogic [7:0] mm_dut;\\n\\tlogic [7:0] ss_ref;\\n\\tlogic [7:0] ss_dut;\\n\\n\\t// State Capture Registers for First Mismatch Display\\n\\treg clk_captured = 0;\\n\\treg reset_captured = 0;\\n\\treg ena_captured = 0;\\n\\treg pm_ref_captured = 0;\\n\\treg pm_dut_captured = 0;\\n\\treg [7:0] hh_ref_captured = 8\'h00;\\n\\treg [7:0] hh_dut_captured = 8\'h00;\\n\\treg [7:0] mm_ref_captured = 8\'h00;\\n\\treg [7:0] mm_dut_captured = 8\'h00;\\n\\treg [7:0] ss_ref_captured = 8\'h00;\\n\\treg [7:0] ss_dut_captured = 8\'h00;\\n\\t\\n\\twire tb_match;\\n\\twire tb_mismatch = ~tb_match;\\n\\t\\n\\t// Dump Waveform\\n\\tinitial begin \\n\\t\\t$dumpfile(\\"wave.vcd\\");\\n\\t\\t$dumpvars(1, stimulus_gen.clk, tb_mismatch, clk, reset, ena, pm_ref, pm_dut, hh_ref, hh_dut, mm_ref, mm_dut, ss_ref, ss_dut );\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\t// Instantiate Stimulus Generator (Controls resets/enables)\\n\\tstimulus_gen stim1 (\\n\\t\\t.clk, \\n\\t\\t.reset, \\n\\t\\tena, \\n\\t\\thh_dut, mm_dut, ss_dut, pm_dut, tb_match, \\n\\t\\twavedrom_title, wavedrom_enable);\\n\\n\\t// Instantiate Reference Model\\t\\n\\tRefModule good1 (\\n\\t\\t.clk, \\n\\t\\t.reset, \\n\\t\\tena, \\n\\t\\t.pm(pm_ref),\\n\\t\\thh(hh_ref),\\n\\t\\t.mm(mm_ref),\\n\\t\\t.ss(ss_ref) );\\n\\t\\n\\t// Instantiate DUT\\t\\n\\tTopModule top_module1 (\\n\\t\\t.clk,\\n\\t\\t.reset,\\n\\t\\tena,\\n\\t\\t.pm(pm_dut),\\n\\t\\thh(hh_dut),\\n\\t\\t.mm(mm_dut),\\n\\t\\tss(ss_dut) );\\n\\n\\t\\n\\t// Helper task to display state upon first error\\n\\ttask display_first_mismatch;\\n\\t\\tbegin\\n\\t\\t\\t$display(\\"========================================================"\n        , "\\n*** FIRST MISMATCH DETECTED AT TIME %0t ps ***\\n\\t\\tSIMULATION FAILED - 1 MISMATCH DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME %0t\\n\\t\\t========================================================"\n        : 2, \n        "$time"\n        : 1\n        , "$time"\n        : 2\n        , "\\n--- Input Signals to DUT ---"\n        : 3\n        , "$clk: %b (Width: 1)"\n        : 4\n        , "$reset: %b (Width: 1)"\n        : 5\n        , "$ena: %b (Width: 1)"\n        : 6\n        , "$pm_ref: %b (Width: 1)"\n        : 7\n        , "$hh_ref: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 8\n        , "$mm_ref: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 9\n        , "$ss_ref: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 10\n        , "\\n--- Output Signals (DUT) ---"\n        : 11\n        , "$pm_dut: %b (Width: 1)"\n        : 12\n        , "$hh_dut: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 13\n        , "$mm_dut: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 14\n        , "$ss_dut: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 15\n        , "\\n--- Expected Output Signals (Reference) ---"\n        : 16\n        , "$pm_ref: %b (Width: 1)"\n        : 17\n        , "$hh_ref: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 18\n        , "$mm_ref: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 19\n        , "$ss_ref: %h (%b) (Width: 8)"\n        : 20\n        , "\\n========================================================"\n        : 21\n        , "\\nEnd of Mismatch Report."\n        : 22\n        , "\\n========================================================"\n        : 23\n        , "\\nEnd of Mismat